node.title: Deep Learning for Time Series Forecasting, Anomaly Detection and Classification
node.description:
Please register here to receive zoom join link.
https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2021111513
(Free online tech event, you can join from anywhere. after register at the event website, you will receive the join link. also receive recordings if you miss the live sessions. thanks)

description:
Deep learning has made impressive strides with respect to time series forecasting and classification. DL models have recently shattered time-series research benchmarks yet remain seldom used in the industry.

In this seminar, we will discuss how to use deep learning to forecast and classify real world time series datasets in healthcare, climate, and agriculture using Flow Forecast, a deep learning for time series framework built in PyTorch. We will also discuss some of the latest advances and cutting edge research in the time series field.

node.title: Online Webinar: Migrating from Oracle to PostgreSQL
node.description:
Please register here to receive zoom join link.
https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2021110410

(Free online tech event, you can join from anywhere. after register at the event website, you will receive the join link. also receive recordings if you miss the live sessions. thanks)

Description:
Is your organization exploring the option of using PostgreSQL as an alternative to Oracle database? There are a number of features that make PostgreSQL a more compelling database platform. Oracle is a popular database management system but it does not utilize the power of true open source. The use of PostgreSQL is the latest result of the adoption of open source by a growing number of companies to avoid vendor lock-ins and take on the cost savings.
In this webinar we will look at:
- The Features and Benefits of PostgreSQL.
- Requirements for beginning the process of migration.
- Breakdown of the steps necessary in the migration process.
- Best practices and strategies to benefit your migration process.

Who should attend:
This webinar is meant to provide an overview of the benefits of migrating to PostgreSQL and how to do so from a Oracle database. By the end of the webinar attendees will grasp a better understanding of how PostgreSQL compares to Oracle and what considerations and steps are necessary to the migration process. The following individuals will benefit from the concepts discussed in this presentation:
- CTO / Business Leaders
- VP of Data or Infrastructure
- Database Administrators
- Data Engineers

node.title: AWS AI/ML Series: Future Industrial Operations with Machine Learning
node.description:
Join us to win AWS credits. We are partnering with AWS team to host a series of AI/ML tech seminars for the community. This is the first session.
** registration instruction ***
RSVP: https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2021101119
(Note: you will NOT receive zoom join link if you don't register at the website. thanks).

Abstract:
This talk will discuss decision making for industrial operations with Self-Supervised Learning (SSL) and Reinforcement Learning (RL). Self-supervised learning holds a lot of promise to build robust machine learning models without massive amounts of labelled data.

Reinforcement learning presents a formal framework for sequential decision-making. Thanks to the recent success of deep neural networks, research into both SSL and RL has enjoyed remarkable achievements.
This talk will briefly share our journey on using SSL and RL to automate and optimise industrial operations. It will also highlight some prescriptive guidance on accelerating production-ready machine learning pipelines on AWS.

We will give away a few AWS credits during the event.

node.title: 4-Weeks AI course: Full Stack Deep Learning in AWS (Cohort 13)
node.description:
This is paid online course (using zoom), follow instructions below to enroll.
-----------
4-weeks AI course: Full Stack Deep Learning in AWS (Cohort 13)
Start date: Sep 21st，10AM PDT (GMT-7), Every Tue/Thu.

Enrollment:
https://www.aicamp.ai/course/coursedetails/C2021092110

In the AICamp online classroom (powered by Zoom), we will meet twice a week and you will interact with instructors and other classmates, listen the lectures, discuss problems; After class, you will work on projects, homework, and get support on private group on slack.

The course include:
* 4 weeks/ 8 sessions/ 12 hours
* 8 lectures / 8 hands-on projects
* Live Sessions, Real time interaction
* Capstone projects, work with peer students globally
* Slack supports to projects and homework

Details:
Many deep learning course cover theoretical techniques of algorithms and modeling. In this course, we will train you to become a Full Stack Deep Learning Engineer, capable of not just training models but also deploying and managing them in production for business value.
Building projects is the best way both to test the skills you have acquired and to demonstrate your newfound abilities to future employers.

You will learn deep learning primarily through building 8 production grade services, step by step. You will learn how to build production AI in AWS, how to integrate it with an application, and how to manage it through its lifecycle.
You will also build from scratch a custom project (where you will gather image data, train and tune a production grade neural network, build a prediction service, and connect that prediction service to create your own image processing AI application).

Students who take this course will be able to:
* Identify and frame business use cases that can be solved by deep learning
* Choose the right techniques, tools, frameworks to the business use cases
* Build production AI on AWS, and manage through their lifecycle.
* Hands on implementation of end to end AI for each use cases

node.title: Online webinar: The Advantages of Migrating to OpenSearch
node.description:
*** Register and attend link:
https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2021083110
(This event is hosted at the US pacific time zone, still register to receive the recordings if you can't attend the live session)

Abstract:
Is your organization data driven and do you need a strategy to search and analyse the growing data? Several solutions are available for you to manage search and analytics, with Elasticsearch being one of them. Elasticsearch is a proven search and analytics engine but you will be surprised to know that it is not a truly open source offering. If you are one of the growing list of companies that embrace open source software for cost savings and superior technology and like to avoid vendor lock-ins, then you have a better alternative in OpenSearch. OpenSearch project is a community-driven, open source fork of Elasticsearch and Kibana.
In this webinar we will look at:
- Why OpenSearch is a better alternative to Elasticsearch.
- OpenSearch feature set and how it compares against Elasticsearch.
- Common Use Cases for OpenSearch.
- Deployment considerations and best practices.

Who should attend?
The workshop is geared towards providing an overview of OpenSearch as an analytics and search platform. Attendees will gain insight on how OpenSearch stacks up against elasticsearch, it’s feature set and use cases. Following individuals will benefit from the webinar
- CTO / Business leaders.
- VP of Data or Infrastructure.
- Director of Data Platforms.
- Data Engineers
